<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900411-0054</DOCNO><DOCID>900411-0054.</DOCID><HL>   Taiwan to Open Reserves</HL><DATE>04/11/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B6</SO><CO>   FREST</CO><IN>MONETARY NEWS, FOREIGN EXCHANGE, TRADE (MON)BANKS (BNK)INTERNATIONAL ECONOMIC NEWS AND STATISTICS (IEN)</IN><LP>   TAIPEI, Taiwan -- The Central Bank announced that it willappropriate a part of Taiwan's foreign exchange reserves torefinance Taiwanese businesses that plan to invest or seekmergers and acquisitions overseas.   The move is aimed at using Taiwan's approximately $73billion in local foreign exchange reserves to expand Taiwan'seconomic base and stimulate further development, Yu Chen, theCentral Bank's deputy governor, said at a news conference. Hesaid the move might trigger short-term capital outflow, butin the longer term, earnings from overseas investment arelikely to extend Taiwan's economic strength.</LP><TEXT>   Those eligible for the loans include companies involved innatural resource development, high technology, anti-pollutiontechnology, and management training, he said. The Bank ofCommunications, Export-Import Bank of the Republic of China,International Commercial Bank of China and the ChinaDevelopment Corp. are the four banks designated to issue theloans.</TEXT></DOC>